pros:
- Good pay for entry level jobs;
- No absurd goals for bank tellers, like many other banks have;
- Really good benefits, with matching RRSP and TFSA, including for part-time employees;
- Good career path progression, if you are willing to move around;
- Really good people (team dependent).

cons:
- Too much bureaucracy which makes your job slower;
- Depends heavily on an inefficient back office team, everything takes forever to get done and they hardly ever hear you.
- At times it feels that no one knows what is going on, how specific things are done, or why they are done that way.
- General lack of support;
- Incredibly old technology.
